organic_results.title: A dynamic analysis of educational attainment
organic_results.snippet: This paper traces the educational attainment experiences of a cohort of young men in the Pacific Northwest between the ages of 16 and 31. The experiences of this cohort reveal that a college degree is the net result of movement through a complex series of steps. We traced the movement of the cohort through these steps and found that completion of a college degree and graduate school attendance required success at every stage in the process.
